parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft actuator bolts can cause the engine to stop operating, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents, especially if the failure occurs at high speeds.
The flawed design of the coolant pipe can cause a massive coolant leak, leading to engine overheating and potentially causing engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stoppage due to Camshaft Controller Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft controller can cause the engine to stop operating, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents, especially if the failure occurs at high speeds.
The failure of the transfer case can cause sudden jerking, hesitation, or loss of acceleration, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Grinding or clunking sounds when driving
surging or pausing when shifting gears
feeling of the vehicle lurching forward or backward

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Coolant System Failure due to Faulty Plastic Tubing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic tubing in the coolant system can cause coolant leaks, leading to overheating and potential engine damage.
symptoms: Coolant leaks while the vehicle is stationary

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to lose power and performance, leading to potential safety risks while driving.
symptoms: "Hybrid system failure" message appears on the dashboard
error message may disappear and resurface randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transfer Case Failure in AWD Vehicles
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, leading to uneven wear on the front and rear differentials and potential transmission damage.
symptoms: uneven wear on front and rear differentials
